  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance - Country-Level Funding - IOM 2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project addresses life-saving humanitarian needs both inside Protection of Civilians (PoC) sites and support rapid response mechanisms which provide life-saving health services to conflict-affected populations in hard-to-access areas. In particular, through this project, IOM is assisting the conflict-affected populations through a multi-sector approach encompassing Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM), shelter and Non-Food Items (NFI) assistance, as well as Protection support to Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) and vulnerable host communities across South Sudan. These efforts will be underpinned by IOM&#x2019;s Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM), which has established itself as the key actor providing updated information on the numbers, locations and priority needs of IDPs and returnees, combined with analyses of the migration dynamics in the country and biometric data management to support evidence-based decisions and accountable delivery of assistance.</narrative>
  </description>
